The paper deals with state estimation in power distribution systems, which involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms to estimate the system state based on measurements. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed method uses matrix completion and optimization techniques to estimate the system state, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) concepts. The low-rank characteristics of the matrix are explored, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The method is designed to handle bad data and improve robustness, which is a common problem in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the proposed method in power distribution systems, which involves system integration and implementation (cs.SI).
